main event: A strange object was observed near Dover Air Force Base in Delaware on February 22, 1953.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 4-5 degrees above the horizon and was moving northward over the town of Frederic, Delaware.
The object appeared to be approaching and changed colors, turning white, green, and red at various times.
The object was estimated to be moving at a speed of 500-600 mph.
The object was visible to the base theater officer but not to the tower personnel.
The officer believed the object was manned and had superior performance capabilities.
location: near Dover Air Force Base, Delaware
